507
00:30:56,554 --> 00:30:58,818
Fucking fire inspector.

508
00:31:00,458 --> 00:31:03,256
What's next, the mailman?

509
00:31:10,568 --> 00:31:13,264
l can't take it, Otto.

510
00:31:13,304 --> 00:31:15,829
l can't take it
when it's all over the street.

511
00:31:15,874 --> 00:31:17,398
l'm going to have to get
Hines to deal with this.

512
00:31:17,442 --> 00:31:20,411
-lt'll cost.
-Do what you have to do.

513
00:31:20,445 --> 00:31:21,673
DUTCH^
lf l have to go to trial...

514
00:31:21,713 --> 00:31:23,840
l'm not going to trial
in the city.

515
00:31:23,882 --> 00:31:26,316
l want it in the boondocks.

516
00:31:26,351 --> 00:31:29,047
Oh, Bo...

517
00:31:29,087 --> 00:31:31,647
what have you done to me?

518
00:31:31,689 --> 00:31:33,782
Close the door.

519
00:31:35,360 --> 00:31:37,089
BlLLY^ Mr. Berman.

520
00:31:37,128 --> 00:31:39,756
What are we going to do?
He killed that man.

521
00:31:39,797 --> 00:31:41,594
Forget it.
You didn't see anything.

522
00:31:41,633 --> 00:31:42,964
You didn't hear anything.
Nothing happened.

523
00:31:43,001 --> 00:31:47,131
You even think about it again,
you're as good as dead.

524
00:31:47,171 --> 00:31:51,164
Listen to me, kid.
You're the upcoming generation.

525
00:31:51,209 --> 00:31:52,972
Things are going
to be different for you.

526
00:31:53,011 --> 00:31:56,037
You need different skills
from these guys.

527
00:31:56,080 --> 00:31:58,878
lt'll be streamlined--
not so much fire in the street.

528
00:31:58,917 --> 00:32:00,384
And when that happens,
if you're lucky...

529
00:32:00,418 --> 00:32:02,818
