for your mother.

541
00:32:40,091 --> 00:32:41,285
Where am l going?

542
00:32:41,326 --> 00:32:43,988
Mr. Schultz is having
a trial coming up...

543
00:32:44,028 --> 00:32:47,259
and we have decided
he'll get a better deal...

544
00:32:47,298 --> 00:32:49,129
if the trial
takes place upstate.

545
00:32:49,167 --> 00:32:50,532
ls that all right with you?

546
00:32:52,003 --> 00:32:53,732
And l want you
to buy a book to read.

547
00:32:53,771 --> 00:32:55,329
What do l need a book for?

548
00:32:55,373 --> 00:32:57,773
You gonna do what l say
or give me a hard time?

549
00:32:59,577 --> 00:33:00,874
-Mr. Berman?
-Yes?

550
00:33:00,912 --> 00:33:02,880
Who is this man you're meeting?

551
00:33:02,914 --> 00:33:06,350
lf you want to stay
in the crime business, kid...

552
00:33:06,384 --> 00:33:09,410
you got to stop asking
all these questions.

553
00:33:09,454 --> 00:33:11,786
[Car approaches]

554
00:33:15,460 --> 00:33:18,520
His name is Hines.

555
00:33:18,563 --> 00:33:21,555
He's a district leader
for Tammany Hall.

556
00:33:21,599 --> 00:33:23,226
<i>He's on our payroll...</i>

557
00:33:23,267 --> 00:33:26,566
<i>takes care of problems</i>
<i>like this.</i>

558
00:33:26,604 --> 00:33:27,901
[Car door closes]

559
00:33:29,674 --> 00:33:31,665
[Ship horn blows]

560
00:33:33,978 --> 00:33:35,843
<i>HlNES: So, Otto,</i>
<i>you're looking good.</i>

561
00:33:35,880 --> 00:33:39,008
Good to see you.
lt's a pleasure.

562
00:33:41,986 --> 00:33:43,977
[Speaking indistinctly]

563
00:33:46,824 --> 00:33:48,883
[Dog barking]

564
00:33:48,926 --> 00:33:52,123
<i>BlLLY: These guys ain't like</i>
<i>anybody you ever met.</i>

565
00:33:52,163 --> 00:33:54,688
<i>They want something--</i>
<i>boom--it gets done.</i>

566
00:33:54,732 --> 00:33:55,994
And the money--l swear...

567
00:33:56,034 --> 00:33:57,763
you never seen money
like this in your life.

568
00:33:57,802 --> 00:33:59,793
So what?
How much money can you spend?

569
00:33:59,837 --> 00:34:01,395
That ain't the point.

570
00:34:01,439 --> 00:34:03,805
Let me tell you,
money can do anything.

571
00:34:03,841 --> 00:34:05,775
l bet you never had
anything in your life...

572
00:34:05,810 --> 00:34:08,404
that somebody else
didn't wear first.

573
00:34:15,019 --> 00:34:18,455
Here.
Get yourself something nice.

574
00:34:19,824 --> 00:34:22,292
Come on, Arnold,
we're having a party.

575
00:34:22,326 --> 00:34:24,487
-Where?
-Where do you think?

576
00:34:24,529 --> 00:34:26,019
<i>ARNOLD: Just don't break</i>
<i>anything this time.</i>

577
00:34:26,064 --> 00:34:27,156
<i>BlLLY: Don't worry.</i>

578
00:34:27,198 --> 00:34:29,189
[People chattering]

579
00:34:31,636 --> 00:34:33,263
Hello.

580
00:34:35,773 --> 00:34:38,003
Mr. Klein, how are you?

581
00:34:38,042 --> 00:34:39,839
<i>KLElN:</i>
<i>Look at you, wearing a suit.</i>

582
00:34:39,877 --> 00:34:41,936
Mr. Rosen, you're looking good.

583
00:34:41,979 --> 00:34:43,970
-How are you?
-Very good.

584
00:34:45,349 --> 00:34:47,476
Girls, girls, girls.

585
00:34:52,523 --> 00:34:54,491
-Hey, Charlie.
-Hello, Billy.

586
00:34:54,525 --> 00:34:56,618
-Hey, Mrs. Thomas.
-Hello, Billy.

587
00:34:56,661 --> 00:34:59,596
-Billy, don't you look swell?
-Thank you.

588
00:34:59,630 --> 00:35:00,927
Hi, Ma.

589
00:35:02,166 --> 00:35:03,963
l got a job.

590
00:35:04,001 --> 00:35:08,404
The thing is,
it's in the country--upstate.

591
00:35:08,439 --> 00:35:10,873
<i>lt's just for the summer.</i>

592
00:35:10,908 --> 00:35:13,206
<i>Ma?</i>

593
00:35:16,647 --> 00:35:18,911
This is for you.

594
00:35:18,950 --> 00:35:22,909
Billy Behan, look at you--

595
00:35:22,954 --> 00:35:26,390
the richest man
on Bathgate Avenue.

596
00:35:26,424 --> 00:35:28,324
[Chattering]

597
00:35:28,359 --> 00:35:30,190
[Music playing]

598
00:36:45,570 --> 00:36:46,764
[Sighs]

599
00:37:00,618 --> 00:37:01,778
[Both laugh]

600
00:37:01,819 --> 00:37:02,843
You're bad.

601
00:37:04,121 --> 00:37:05,884
DUTCH^ Let's go to work.

602
00:37:14,098 --> 00:37:17,829
-lrving.
-Miss, this way.

603
00:37:17,868 --> 00:37:21,099
What?
What's the matter?

604
00:37:21,138 --> 00:37:23,231
-Come on.
-Bo, what's going on?

605
00:37:23,274 --> 00:37:25,265
[Car engine idling]

606
